Blessed is he who is concerned for the weak;
\q in the day of trouble, Yahweh will rescue him.
\q

6:
If my enemy comes to see me, he says worthless things;
\q his heart gathers up my disaster for itself;
\q when he goes away from me, he tells others about it.

7:
All who hate me whisper together against me;
\q against me they hope for my hurt.
\q

8:
They say, "An evil disease holds on tightly to him;
\q now that he is lying down, he will rise up no more."
\q
